## 6. BookingCalendar UI

Deux patterns selon besoin :

- **Lecture seule** (affichage dispo sur fiche) → `FullCalendar` background events, c'est ce qu'utilise DIAMANTNOIR (`components/booking/AvailabilityCalendar.tsx`).
- **Sélection de dates** (checkout) → `react-day-picker` v8 en `range mode`, léger, accessible, contrôlable.

```tsx
// components/booking/DateRangePicker.tsx
'use client';
import { DayPicker, type DateRange } from 'react-day-picker';
import { fr } from 'date-fns/locale';
import { differenceInDays } from 'date-fns';

interface Props {
  propertyId: string;
  minNights: number;
  maxNights: number;
  blockedRanges: Array<{ start: Date; end: Date }>;
  onSelect: (range: DateRange | undefined) => void;
}

export function DateRangePicker({ minNights, maxNights, blockedRanges, onSelect }: Props) {
  const disabled = [
    { before: new Date() },
    ...blockedRanges.map(r => ({ from: r.start, to: r.end })),
  ];

  return (
    <DayPicker
      mode="range"
      locale={fr}
      numberOfMonths={2}
      disabled={disabled}
      onSelect={(range) => {
        if (range?.from && range?.to) {
          const nights = differenceInDays(range.to, range.from);
          if (nights < minNights || nights > maxNights) return;
        }
        onSelect(range);
      }}
    />
  );
}
```

**À éviter** : date inputs HTML natifs sur desktop pour le range. OK pour mobile (clavier natif OS) — pattern DIAMANTNOIR `PriceCalculator.tsx` l'assume.

