## 11. Gestion des statuts

Machine d'états stricte. Seules ces transitions sont autorisées :

| De        | Vers         | Trigger                          |
|-----------|--------------|----------------------------------|
| `pending` | `confirmed`  | Webhook `checkout.session.completed` |
| `pending` | `cancelled`  | Webhook `checkout.session.expired` OU action admin |
| `confirmed` | `cancelled`| Action guest (via token, si politique le permet) OU admin |
| `cancelled` | `refunded` | Admin + Stripe refund |
| `confirmed` | `completed`| Cron quotidien, quand `end_date < today` |
| `confirmed` | `no_show`  | Admin seul |

Encoder via un helper + triggers Postgres en complément :

```ts
// lib/booking/state-machine.ts
const ALLOWED: Record<string, string[]> = {
  pending: ['confirmed', 'cancelled'],
  confirmed: ['cancelled', 'completed', 'no_show'],
  cancelled: ['refunded'],
  completed: [],
  refunded: [],
  no_show: [],
};

export function canTransition(from: string, to: string): boolean {
  return ALLOWED[from]?.includes(to) ?? false;
}
```

